cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the use of sequence alignment for information extraction, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the evaluation of a system, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of context windows, which is a common topic in ML and AI (Artificial Intelligence), making cs.AI a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the system using the CoNLL-2003 named entity recognition (NER) task, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
